Key Match Events: David Warner and Travis Head ransacked 70 runs inside the first five overs
Pat Cummins sent down a masterful two for 23 from four overs
Adam Zampa spun his way to two for 28
Mitchell Marsh and his side then slammed the brakes on England to restrict them to 165 for six
Pre-Game Insights: Jos Buttler’s defending champions have been plunged into a world of net run-rate calculations and weather forecasts
Post-Match Reflections: England, desperate to change the tune after that bleak 50-over World Cup last winter, are once again in a bit of strife
Buttler claimed afterwards that Jacks was a call based on “gut feel” – not data – but it set the tone for a scrappy time in the field
Miscellaneous Highlights: England’s destiny out of their hands after poor display
Australia, already a victory over Oman to the good before this one, will be chuckling at the predicament that England now find themselves in
Others: The conditions also made it all the more baffling that, after a tight first over from Moeen Ali, Buttler asked the far less experienced off-spinner, Will Jacks, to share the new ball and defend that trickier end
